<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="e33f662a-e529-4c9f-88e9-34d6b3ec5687" >

    <ol> 
 <li>Navigate to your root folder<br> </li> 
 <li>Find “<a href="/content/ryerson/websupport/responsive-templates/inherited-content-template.html">inheritedContent</a>” file&nbsp;<br> </li> 
 <li>Open file&nbsp; &nbsp;<br> </li> 
 <li>Double click on the area “Sample Site Title” to open the component – don’t click on the text “Sample site Title” (it’s a link!)</li> 
 <li>Change title to reflect site’s name e.g. About Ryerson</li> 
 <li>Create new or new predefined footer<br> </li> 
 <li>If you have site content for the right or left sidebars, this can be added within the left or right sections; it will then display on all pages within your site</li> 
 <li>Click OK</li> 
 <li>Close file</li> 
</ol> 
<p>Related:</p> 
